  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support the Strengthening of the Protection Environment for People Displaced from Venezuela to Brazil and Colombia, as a Key Contribution to Preventing Instability, Increasing Resilience and Building National Crisis Response Capacity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to enhance the capacity of national, local governmentand civil society organizations (CSOs) to face current and possible future crisis, namely by ensuring sufficient access to trainings, response mechanisms and basic management tools. IOM will do so by: (1)improving protection process and documentation of Venezuelans and returning nationals through enhanced access to relevant information and/or to registration; (2) Contribute to have Community response systems in place, public attitude towards persons of concern is improved, co-existence promoted, and basic services for persons with specific needs are met. IOM will also strengthen the capacity of the Government responses and effective coordination with international and national humanitarian actors ensured to support Venezuelans. Further, risk of forced recruitment of children and Gender Based Violence (GBV) will be reduced and quality of response will be enhanced through this project.</narrative>
  </description>
